(33, 1, '2014-04-08 16:29:05', '2014-04-08 16:29:05', '<div class="col-md-6">Faced with technologically-savvy consumers and agile new competitors, financial services organizations are increasingly looking to their internal IT functions to design and deliver innovative new services. But in fast-changing environment, how can you identify and prioritize the innovations that will meet the organization’s strategic objectives and deliver the best returns?An Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can help your IT organization to balance technological innovation with the need to maintain and develop existing, business-critical systems. With a clearer view of all assets across the enterprise, IT functions can improve project selection, execution, and success-while optimizing resources to support continued innovation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">Oracle’s Instantis EnterpriseTrack is a leading, cloud-based PPM solution that can help you to:\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n	<li>Deliver winning products and services</li>\r\n	<li>Prioritize the most promising development projects</li>\r\n	<li>Optimize work and resource management</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate continuous improvement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nExplore the resources below to discover how EPPM is enabling financial institutions to deliver true service innovation.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Service Innovation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-08 16:29:05', '2014-04-08 16:29:05', '', 13, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(34, 1, '2014-04-08 16:29:15', '2014-04-08 16:29:15', '<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nThe continuing financial crisis in some geographies, combined with the mounting debt problems of the world’s largest economies, is causing ongoing market uncertainty for large financial institutions. Strategic changes are required if banks are to raise their ROE back into double figures. But strategic changes must also be translated into effective action - something that is often easier said than done.\r\n\r\nAn effective Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can create a virtuous circle between strategy formulation and strategy execution, creating an environment in which strategy is turned into KPIs and KPIs into business initiatives that are implemented, managed and monitored in an effective and consistent fashion.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\nBy aligning strategy and execution, an EPPM solution can help financial institutions to:\r\n\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n<li>Ensure resources and budgets are aligned with strategic objectives Identify and capitalise on growth opportunities</li>\r\n<li>Boost operating efficiency and reduce operating costs</li>\r\n<li>Increase margins and return on equity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBrowse the resources below to see how a world-class EPPM solution can translate strategic aims into effective action - and monitor the results of those actions to inform future strategy changes.\r\n</div>', 'Strategic Efficiency', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '25-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-08 16:29:15', '2014-04-08 16:29:15', '', 25, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/25-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(36, 1, '2014-04-09 17:03:29', '2014-04-09 17:03:29', '<h1>Financial Services Overview</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nWith economic turbulence creating an uncertain business environment, financial services organizations need to attract and retain customers and gain greater visibility of their operations. At the same time, disruptive new entrants are capturing market share with innovative online and mobile products. Established financial services organizations must develop new offers to maintain competitive advantage. To do so, they need to innovate while ensuring service quality meets customer expectations.\r\n\r\nFinally, regulators are making compliance tougher. Governments and international bodies are introducing new rules and modifying existing ones at an accelerating rate. Financial organizations must be able to keep up with the changes on a global basis, ensure they are implemented, and demonstrate effective risk management.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nFinancial services firms need to be on top of a complex array of projects and priorities in order to stave off new competitors, meet compliance obligations, and impress new and existing customers. Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) answers these challenges by putting executives in command of a multitude of strategic initiatives and measuring performance against strategic goals.\r\n\r\nExplore the resources on this site to discover how EPPM is enabling financial services organizations to stay ahead in a rapidly changing business environment.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'FSI Overview', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'home', '', '', '2014-06-30 15:40:06', '2014-06-30 15:40:06', '', 0, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/?page_id=36', 0, 'page', '', 0),
