(87, 1, '2014-04-23 10:03:48', '2014-04-23 10:03:48', '<h1>FSI Overview</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">With economic turbulence creating an uncertain business environment, financial services organizations need to attract and retain customers and gain greater visibility of their operationsAt the same time, disruptive new entrants are capturing market share with innovative online and mobile products. Established financial services organizations must develop new offers to maintain competitive advantage. To do so, they need to innovate while ensuring service quality meets customer expectations.\r\n\r\nFinally, regulators are making compliance tougher. Governments and international bodies are introducing new rules and modifying existing ones at an accelerating rate. Financial organizations must be able to keep up with the changes on a global basis, ensure they are implemented, and demonstrate effective risk management.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">Financial services firms need to be on top of a complex array of projects and priorities in order to stave off new competitors, meet compliance obligations, and impress new and existing customers. Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) answers these challenges by putting executives in command of a multitude of strategic initiatives and measuring performance against strategic goals.Explore the resources on this site to discover how EPPM is enabling financial services organizations to stay ahead in a rapidly changing business environment.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'FSI Overview', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-23 10:03:48', '2014-04-23 10:03:48', '', 36, 'http://oracle.mointernational-clients.co.uk/uncategorized/36-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
