(162, 1, '2014-05-01 10:46:28', '2014-05-01 10:46:28', '<h1>Service Innovation</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nFaced with technologically-savvy consumers and agile new competitors, financial services organizations are increasingly looking to design and deliver innovative new services. But in a fast-changing environment, how can you identify and prioritize the innovations that will meet the organization’s strategic objectives and deliver the best returns?\r\n\r\nAn Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can help your organization balance technological innovation with the need to maintain and develop existing, business-critical systems. With a clearer view of all assets across the enterprise, IT and business functions can improve project selection, execution, and success—while optimizing resources to support continued innovation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nOracle''s Instantis EnterpriseTrack is a leading, cloud-based PPM solution that can help you to:\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n	<li>Prioritize the most promising development projects</li>\r\n	<li>Optimize work and resource management</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate continuous improvement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nExplore the resources below to discover how EPPM is enabling financial institutions to deliver true service innovation.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Service Innovation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-01 10:46:28', '2014-05-01 10:46:28', '', 13, 'http://oracle-eppm.com/fsi/uncategorized/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(163, 1, '2014-05-01 10:54:20', '2014-05-01 10:54:20', '<h1>FSI Overview</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nWith economic turbulence creating an uncertain business environment, financial services organizations need to attract and retain customers and gain greater visibility of their operations. At the same time, disruptive new entrants are capturing market share with innovative online and mobile products. Established financial services organizations must develop new offers to maintain competitive advantage. To do so, they need to innovate while ensuring service quality meets customer expectations.\r\n\r\nFinally, regulators are making compliance tougher. Governments and international bodies are introducing new rules and modifying existing ones at an accelerating rate. Financial organizations must be able to keep up with the changes on a global basis, ensure they are implemented, and demonstrate effective risk management.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n\r\nFinancial services firms need to be on top of a complex array of projects and priorities in order to stave off new competitors, meet compliance obligations, and impress new and existing customers. Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) answers these challenges by putting executives in command of a multitude of strategic initiatives and measuring performance against strategic goals.\r\n\r\nExplore the resources on this site to discover how EPPM is enabling financial services organizations to stay ahead in a rapidly changing business environment.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'FSI Overview', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-01 10:54:20', '2014-05-01 10:54:20', '', 36, 'http://oracle-eppm.com/fsi/uncategorized/36-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(164, 1, '2014-05-01 14:17:58', '2014-05-01 14:17:58', '<h1>Strategic Efficiency</h1>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\nThe continuing financial crisis, combined with the mounting debt problems of the world’s largest economies, is causing ongoing market uncertainty for large financial institutions.  Strategic changes are required if banks are to raise their ROE back into double figures. But strategic changes must also be translated into effective action – something that is often easier said than done.\r\n\r\nAn effective Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (EPPM) solution can create a virtuous circle between strategy formulation and strategy execution, creating an environment in which strategy is turned into KPIs and KPIs into business initiatives that are implemented, managed and monitored in an effective and consistent fashion. \r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6">By aligning strategy and execution, an EPPM solution can help financial institutions:\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\r\n	<li>Ensure resources and budgets are aligned with strategic objectives</li>\r\n	<li>Identify and capitalize on growth opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Measure the performance and value of projects against strategic objectives</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBrowse the resources below to see how a world-class EPPM solution can translate strategic aims into effective action – and monitor the results of those actions to inform future strategy changes.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Strategic Efficiency', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '25-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-01 14:17:58', '2014-05-01 14:17:58', '', 25, 'http://oracle-eppm.com/fsi/uncategorized/25-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(170, 4, '2014-06-11 16:31:39', '2014-06-11 16:31:39', 'Financial services companies that are facing uncertain times should consider how to make leaders accountable for identifying and shutting down poorly performing initiatives, focusing resources on projects that promise the greatest return. This will enable them to pursue more opportunities-with the accompanying risks-while minimizing the impact of failures that can have significant consequences for their reputation and capital. But this will require executives to take a hard look at how they manage projects and track risks, so that they can more effectively determine whether an initiative is worth continuing.\n\n<a href="http://www.oracle.com/webapps/dialogue/ns/dlgwelcome.jsp?p_ext=Y&amp;p_dlg_id=15561384&amp;src=7867171&amp;Act=54" target="_blank">Read the Economist Intelligence Unit (EIU) Research Report</a>: "Preemptive Action: Mitigating Project Portfolio Risks in the Financial Services Industry".\n<ul class="list-unstyled custom-list">\n	<li>Discover strategies for minimizing project risk</li>\n	<li>Drive efficient project management</li>\n	<li>Gain competitive</li>\n</ul>', 'Preemptive action Mitigating project portfolio risks in the financial services industry', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '159-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-06-11 16:31:39', '2014-06-11 16:31:39', '', 159, 'http://oracle-eppm.com/fsi/uncategorized/159-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
